# Cloudflare credentials for deploying the plan-server Worker.
# Copy to `.cloudflare.env` in this directory, fill in, then: chmod 600 .cloudflare.env
#
# Deliberately NOT named `.env`: wrangler treats a `.env` file as a source of
# Worker *secrets* and binds its contents into the deployed Worker's runtime
# environment. A Cloudflare API token has no business inside the Worker it
# deploys, so it lives in a file wrangler does not read, and `deploy.sh` exports
# it into the process environment instead.
#
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
#   Create at https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
#   Use the "Edit Cloudflare Workers" template (NOT the Pages template —
#   a Pages-scoped token cannot create a Worker or a Durable Object).
#
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID
#   Shown in the Cloudflare dashboard sidebar.

CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
